article:
The term 'antiparallel' may refer to: *Antiparallel (biochemistry), the
orientation of adjacent molecules *Antiparallel (mathematics), the placement of
parallel lines in relation to an angle *Antiparallel (physics), vectors that lie
along parallel lines but point in opposite directions *Antiparallel
(electronics), the polarity of devices run in parallel
* "Antiparallel" can also be used to describe two parallel one-way streets in
  which traffic is traveling in opposing directions.
